        "content": "<p>Precisely, a limit is not just an object, but it is defined as a (universal) cone. </p>\n<p>So a functor <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>F</mi><mspace></mspace><mspace width=\"0.1111111111111111em\"></mspace><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0.17em\"></mo><mtext> ⁣</mtext><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\">:</mo><mspace width=\"0.3333333333333333em\"></mspace><mi mathvariant=\"script\">C</mi><mo>⟶</mo><mi mathvariant=\"script\">D</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">F\\colon \\mathcal{C}\\longrightarrow \\mathcal{D}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.69433em;vertical-align:-0.011em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"mspace nobreak\"></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1111111111111111em;\"></span><span class=\"mpunct\"></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:-0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mrel\">:</span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.3333333333333333em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05834em;\">C</span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">⟶</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">D</span></span></span></span></span> preserves a limit <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>p</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">(x,p)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">x</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">p</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span> of a diagram <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>J</mi><mspace></mspace><mspace width=\"0.1111111111111111em\"></mspace><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0.17em\"></mo><mtext> ⁣</mtext><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\">:</mo><mspace width=\"0.3333333333333333em\"></mspace><mi mathvariant=\"script\">I</mi><mo>⟶</mo><mi mathvariant=\"script\">C</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">J\\colon \\mathcal{I}\\longrightarrow \\mathcal{C}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.69433em;vertical-align:-0.011em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.09618em;\">J</span><span class=\"mspace nobreak\"></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1111111111111111em;\"></span><span class=\"mpunct\"></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:-0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mrel\">:</span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.3333333333333333em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07382em;\">I</span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">⟶</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05834em;\">C</span></span></span></span></span> (where <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">x</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.43056em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">x</span></span></span></span> is an object of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"script\">C</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathcal{C}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05834em;\">C</span></span></span></span></span> and <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>p</mi><mo>=</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><msub><mi>p</mi><mi>i</mi></msub><mspace></mspace><mspace width=\"0.1111111111111111em\"></mspace><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0.17em\"></mo><mtext> ⁣</mtext><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\">:</mo><mspace width=\"0.3333333333333333em\"></mspace><mi>x</mi><mo>⟶</mo><mi>J</mi><mi>i</mi><msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mrow><mi>i</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"script\">I</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">p=(p_i\\colon x\\longrightarrow Ji)_{i\\in\\mathcal{I}}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.19444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">p</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">p</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.31166399999999994em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathdefault mtight\">i</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace nobreak\"></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1111111111111111em;\"></span><span class=\"mpunct\"></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:-0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mrel\">:</span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.3333333333333333em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">x</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">⟶</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.09618em;\">J</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">i</span><span class=\"mclose\"><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.32833099999999993em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathdefault mtight\">i</span><span class=\"mrel mtight\">∈</span><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathcal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.07382em;\">I</span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.17737em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> is the edges of a cone) if and only if <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>F</mi><mi>x</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>F</mi><mi>p</mi><mo>=</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>F</mi><msub><mi>p</mi><mi>i</mi></msub><msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mrow><mi>i</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"script\">I</mi></mrow></msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">(Fx, Fp=(Fp_i)_{i\\in\\mathcal{I}})</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">x</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">p</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">p</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.31166399999999994em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathdefault mtight\">i</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose\"><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.32833099999999993em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathdefault mtight\">i</span><span class=\"mrel mtight\">∈</span><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathcal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.07382em;\">I</span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.17737em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span> is a limit of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>F</mi><mo>∘</mo><mi>J</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">F\\circ J</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">∘</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.09618em;\">J</span></span></span></span>. </p>\n<p>This is equivalent to (the existence of a limit <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>y</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>q</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">(y,q)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">y</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">q</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span> of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>F</mi><mo>∘</mo><mi>J</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">F\\circ J</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">∘</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.09618em;\">J</span></span></span></span> in <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"script\">D</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathcal{D}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">D</span></span></span></span></span> and) the existence of an isomorphism <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>F</mi><mi>x</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>F</mi><mi>p</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>≅</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>y</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>q</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">(Fx,Fp)\\cong (y,q)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">x</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">p</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">≅</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">y</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">q</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span> of cones because, in general, a cone is a limit cone if and only if it is isomorphic to some limit cone.</p>",
        "id": 197880031,
        "sender_full_name": "Soichiro Fujii",
        "timestamp": 1589765046
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>In response to the original question, which may have turned out not to be what you <em>meant</em> to ask: the paper <a href=\"https://www.cl.cam.ac.uk/~gw104/preservation.pdf\">Limit Preservation from Naturality</a> by Caccamo–Winskel describes sufficient conditions for such an isomorphism to imply limit-preservation.</p>",
        "id": 197933569,
        "sender_full_name": "Nathanael Arkor",
        "timestamp": 1589808295
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think this maybe obscures the main point though; if <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>C</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">C</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">C</span></span></span></span> and <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>D</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">D</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">D</span></span></span></span> have limits, then for any functor <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>F</mi><mo>:</mo><mi>C</mi><mo>→</mo><mi>D</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">F : C \\to D</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">:</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">C</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">D</span></span></span></span>, there's always a canonical map <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>F</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>lim</mi><mo>⁡</mo><mi>J</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>→</mo><mi>lim</mi><mo>⁡</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>F</mi><mo>∘</mo><mi>J</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">F(\\lim J) \\to \\lim (F \\circ J)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mop\">lim</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.09618em;\">J</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mop\">lim</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">∘</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.09618em;\">J</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span> (exercise); <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>F</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">F</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span></span></span></span> preserves the limit of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>J</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">J</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.09618em;\">J</span></span></span></span> if and only if <em>this map</em> is an isomorphism.</p>",
        "id": 197954960,
        "sender_full_name": "Reid Barton",
        "timestamp": 1589817292
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It's somewhat tiresome to write out any of the exact definitions of \"preserves limits\", especially if lacking the vocabulary of limit cones, and so it's common to see abuses like \"<span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>F</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>lim</mi><mo>⁡</mo><mi>J</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>≅</mo><mi>lim</mi><mo>⁡</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>F</mi><mo>∘</mo><mi>J</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">F(\\lim J) \\cong \\lim (F \\circ J)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mop\">lim</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.09618em;\">J</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">≅</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mop\">lim</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">∘</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.09618em;\">J</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span>\" to mean that the canonical map is an isomorphism or \"<span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>F</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">F(x)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">x</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span> is a limit of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>F</mi><mo>∘</mo><mi>J</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">F \\circ J</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">∘</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.09618em;\">J</span></span></span></span>\" to mean via the maps induced by <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>F</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">F</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span></span></span></span> and the cone morphisms for the original limit <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">x</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.43056em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">x</span></span></span></span> and <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>J</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">J</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.09618em;\">J</span></span></span></span>.</p>",
        "id": 197955968,
        "sender_full_name": "Reid Barton",
        "timestamp": 1589817689
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Right, I think this convention that <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo>≅</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\cong</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.589em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">≅</span></span></span></span> is often a <em>canonical</em> isomorphism, rather than an arbitrary one, can be easy to not notice when learning, especially as this is sometimes completely implicit. (The abstract from the paper above makes this clear, though.)</p>",
        "id": 197958074,
        "sender_full_name": "Nathanael Arkor",
        "timestamp": 1589818548
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It's fun to try to dream up examples where <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>F</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></mrow><mi>J</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>≅</mo><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>F</mi><mo>∘</mo><mi>J</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">F(\\mathrm{lim} J) \\cong \\mathrm{lim} (F \\circ J)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">l</span><span class=\"mord mathrm\">i</span><span class=\"mord mathrm\">m</span></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.09618em;\">J</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">≅</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">l</span><span class=\"mord mathrm\">i</span><span class=\"mord mathrm\">m</span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">∘</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.09618em;\">J</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span>, the mere existence of <em>some</em> isomorphism, holds but is not good enough.</p>",
        "id": 197998899,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1589837983
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>on the flip side, Steve Lack has a paper in which he shows that -- contrary to what you'd expect -- in certain special cases <em>some</em> isomorphism is actually good enough <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/0912.2126.pdf\">https://arxiv.org/pdf/0912.2126.pdf</a>.</p>",
        "id": 198031397,
        "sender_full_name": "Philip Saville",
        "timestamp": 1589874384
    }
]